column88: We enjoyed the food, but there was really only enough food for 2 people. It was advertised as being able to feed 2 adults and 2 kids, we had 3 adults and assumed it would stretch to feed us ‚Äì we did the wagamama family meal deal last week via Deliveroo and that worked out great. Ting Thai hadn't really thought this one through. There was a lot of rice (800g of it) but only two small portions of the curry, enough sweet potato fries for two people to get a small share of, and only one piece of the bread ‚Äì enough for one adult. A tiny portion of warm salad was included but didn't make up for this. There really should be a third portion of curry to split between 2 kids or 1 adult, another portion of the sweet potato fries, and at least one, if not two, pieces of the bread to make this a proper family sharing promotion.
column94: Overall it was a good meal, and delivery excellent, but the food portions were not right this time for the type of promotion.

column78: The impression given from the image was of a large portion of food which would feed four people. The crispy cauliflower was shown to have been placed on the curry leading us to expect it to come separately to be added when served. What we received was a very small portion (not even enough for two: and we don't have huge appetites) and the cauliflower was already in the curry so did not remain "crispy". It did taste good though.
column88: If this dish (cauliflower green Thai curry) is to be branded as a family meal, the portion size needs to be improved. I hope we experienced a one-off error: with the food served to us being less than usual. The calories that the dish was supposed to provide suggest that our experience can't have been the norm. Our experience with Bill's chicken schwarma was completely different with plenty of food available, so what we received for the cauliflower green Thai curry was a real shock. The serving size prompted me to complain: the only time I have ever complained about portion sizes for any takeaway ever.
